Consider now the task of pasting sheets together, such that the result is
 continuous as one crosses the cut 
\begin_inset Formula $z>1$
\end_inset 

.
 Some confusion may result here: one must paste together the cut of the
 polylog, and (if any), the cut of the logarithm as well.
 Thus, for example, suppose one is on the 
\begin_inset Formula $g_{1}\cdot\mbox{Li}_{s}\left(z\right)$
\end_inset 

